This is a pre-release of FreevoTTX, which will add Teletext-support
to Freevo, using bmovl to display.

This is what you have to do to compile it:

Get libzvbi from CVS and compile:  (This is until libzvbi v0.2.3 is released)
$ cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.zapping.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/zapping co vbi
$ cd vbi
$ ./autogen.sh
$ make  (no need to make install)

Install Imlib2:
$ emerge imlib2                    (if you run Gentoo, like me;)
or
$ apt-get install libimlib2-dev    (if you run Debian)
or the preferred way for your particular distribution ;)

Edit Makefile and change LIBZVBI_SOURCES to point to the vbi dir if you
ran the cvs-command above somewhere else than in this directory.

Make two FIFOs, one for input and one for output:
$ mkfifo -m 0600 /tmp/ttx-input.fifo
$ mkfifo -m 0600 /tmp/ttx-output.fifo

Run bmovl-patched MPlayer:
$ mplayer <-tv options> -vop bmovl=0:0:/tmp/ttx-output.fifo

Run FreevoTTX:
$ ./FreevoTTX /dev/v4l/vbi0 100 /tmp/ttx-input.fifo /tmp/ttx-output.fifo 640 480

Start sending commands to FreevoTTX.. For example:
$ echo PAGE 340 >>/tmp/ttx-input.fifo
$ echo ALPHA OFF
$ echo BUTTON 6
$ echo BUTTON 0
$ echo BUTTON 0
$ echo PAGE NEXT
$ echo PAGE PREV
$ echo ALPHA TOGGLE
$ echo HIDE BODY
$ echo SHOW BODY
$ echo HOLD ON
$ echo REVEAL ON
$ echo HOLD OFF
$ echo REVEAL TOGGLE

and so on...
